headline: Federal Reserve Keeps Two Rate-Cut Outlook, But S&P 500 Isn't So Sure
summary: Federal Reserve policymakers are standing by their expectation of 50 basis points in rate cuts this year, as forecasts for unemployment and the inflation impact of Trump tariffs were both revised upward.  The S&P 500 finished fractionally lower after Chairman Jerome Powell touted the resilience of the U.S. economy at his usual news conference, lifting the 10-year Treasury yield off its lows.  Financial stocks such as JPMorgan Chase kept a positive tone after the Fed.

headline: Fed Meeting: Policymakers 'In A Pickle' As Jobless Claims Mount; S&P 500 Rises (Live Coverage)
summary: Federal Reserve officials are weighing higher oil prices, mounting jobless claims and weak housing data as they prepare to issue a policy update and new forecasts.  The S&P 500 is moderately higher ahead of the Fed meeting reveal at 2 p.m. ET, with financial stocks such as JPMorgan Chase showing strength.  Chairman Jerome Powell will hold his usual news conference at 2:30 p.m.

headline: How Chase's new Sapphire Reserve credit card compares to rivals

headline: Credit Card Annual Fees Are Going Up. What It Means for the Stocks.
summary: Credit card issuers are trying to attract more higher-end customers with the promise of more rewards.  Chase announced new perks for holders of its Sapphire Reserve credit cards on Tuesday, including a new points boost program, expanded access to airport lounges, and promotional spending credits with partners such as  Apple Lyft DoorDash  StubHub, and Peloton.  The question now, though, is how Chase competitors react to the news of the fee hike.
